overview: The user initiated a request to fix a pull request riddled with
  security flaws, functional bugs, and persistent Vercel deployment failures.
  The agent embarked on a multi-faceted approach, starting with securing admin
  authentication by replacing a trivially forgeable cookie with HMAC-signed
  session tokens, adapting the implementation to use the Web Crypto API for Edge
  Runtime compatibility. API routes were hardened with pagination and export
  limits, while PDF generation bugs related to NaN values, time calculations,
  and hardcoded user data were resolved. The agent also addressed validation for
  time inputs and nullable number fields. A significant portion of the effort
  was dedicated to debugging Vercel deployment issues, which led to discovering
  and fixing a missing DATABASE_URL in the Prisma schema, updating Next.js to
  resolve a critical CVE, and subsequently navigating breaking changes in Prisma
  7 and Next.js 16's linting process. The final critical fix involved
  lazy-loading the Prisma client to prevent build-time connection errors on
  Vercel, ultimately leading to a successful build and deployment.
